terraform functions

- reusable block of code that takes input and perform some operation then returns the output.

different types of functions;

file
validate
lookup
date and time
type conversion
collection
numeric
string

---------------------

some of the inbuilt functions on terraform

upper("hello world") => converts into all upper case as "HELLO WORLD"

lower("HELO WORLD") => lly does opposite to upper function

trim("mani","i") => removes i in the output in this case

replace("hello world"," ", "-") => replaces space between hello world into hello-world

substr("hello",0,3) => trims 0 - 3 elements and o/p will have hel

max(2,3,4,5,11) => prints max value

min(-99,22,44,33) => prints min value

length([1,2,3,4,2]) => prints the length

concat([1,2,3],[11,22,33]) => concatinates both and prints 1,2,3,11,22,33 in the list (vertically)
#won't work on strings

merge({a=1},{b=2}) => merge both as 1, {"a" = 1
                                        "b" = 2}

#works on strings as well

toset(["a","b","a"]) => converting into set which will eleminate duplicates and output as;
toset(["a",
       "b"])

tonumber("25") => coverts string into number 25

tostring(25) => viceversa o/p as "25"

timestamp() => prints date and time

formatdate("DD-MM-YYYY,timestamp()) => gives requested format o/p sa "12-04-2026"